
# My GRUB_INIT_TUNE/Play Commands From Notes App In My Smartphone

I am sharing with you the tunes I have saved in the notes application on my smartphone because I know that my old laptop has a motherboard beeper (system speaker), but programs like BaWaMI and Linux's Beep command do not work to play tunes through the motherboard beeper, only the GRUB bootloader's play command and the GRUB_INIT_TUNE parameter work, and the reason for this problem has not been found for years.

A GRUB_INIT_TUNE uses the following format: tempo [freq duration] [freq duration]â€¦

- **tempo**: is the base for all note durations in beats per minute, 60 gives a second base (60s/60 = 1s), 120 gives a half-second base, etc.
- **freq**: is the frequency (in hertz) of the sound (set 0 to produce a rest)
- **duration**: is the duration of the sound in beats

You can preview the tunes below with the standalone [index.html](https://gistpreview.github.io/?8df042eb4eb5970ba86ba4ba3ed535d9) included in this gist.

Links:
- [Grub Play Command Help](https://www.gnu.org/software/grub/manual/grub/grub.html#play)
- [Notes Frequencies](https://pages.mtu.edu/~suits/notefreqs.html)
- [GRUB_INIT_TUNE Tester](https://breadmaker.github.io/grub-tune-tester/)
